    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">315/10–2050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bonsal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-20T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 20, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2144. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 2127, October 19, repeated London
                    513. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> informs me it is exchanging views
                    today with Chauvel re question <pb facs="0172" n="156" xml:id="pg_156"/>
                    appointment <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Sec-Gen1">Sec-Gen</gloss>. I have been promised statement of
                    position for tomorrow.<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1">In Paris telegram 2157,
                        October 21, 2 p. m., the Embassy cabled that “La Tournelle, Chief Political
                        Affairs French Foreign Office, has informed us that, after discussion with
                        Chauvel, Schuman has given Chauvel complete discretion in dealing with
                        question appointment <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Secretary General.”
                        La Tournelle was informed by the Embassy that “… Secretary would undoubtedly
                        be disappointed that Schuman had not seen fit to issue instructions to
                        French delegation to vote against Indian resolution.” (315/10–2150)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department 2144, repeated information London 516.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonsal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
